This documentation gives IaaS-specific instructions for installing and configuring Elastic Runtime for Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF).


## <a id='overview'></a> Overview

Elastic Runtime is a runtime environment that lets developers develop and manage cloud-native apps and software services. As a part of PCF, it runs on AWS, Azure, GCP, OpenStack, and vSphere infrastructures.

To install Elastic Runtime, you first need to [Deploy BOSH and Ops Manager](./deploy-bosh-om.html).


